********************************************************************
				PREMIA
********************************************************************

PREMIA is a software for pricing and hedging options on assets and interest rates and for calibration of financial models.

It is developped by the MathFi research group, which gathers scientists from INRIA (the french national institute for research in computer science and control), ENPC (CERMICS laboratory on applied mathematics and computing), and the University of Marne la Vallée.


1- The directories

   In directory Src/ you will find the pricing and hedging tools for equity,
   interest rate and energy derivatives in dimension.

   In directory man/, you will find the documentation of the
   algorithms implemented in Premia.
   Please refer to the README file in this directory.



2- Compilation

   *** Compilation under Linux

   To compile Premia under Linux, issue the following commands
   in the top level directory
      ./autogen.sh
      make 

   These commands create an executable PremiaTerm under the
   Unix/ directory and a shared library libpremia.so available in
   the lib directory.

   A few options are available for the configure command, you can get
   a summary of them by running 
      ./configure --help



   *** Compilation under Windows with Cygwin

   Proceede in the same way as compilation under Linux.

   You will need to have installed the folowing Cygwin packages :
      Devel (default packages)
      autoconf*
      automake*
      binutils
      gcc and gcc-g++
      libtool
      make

   The executable generated is PremiaTerm.exe

